[4] Brazil (Ribeirao Preto, Sao Paulo)
Date: Wed 17 Mar 2010
Source: Gazeta de Ribeirao [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.gazetaderibeirao.com.br/conteudo/mostra_noticia.asp?noticia=1678765&area=92020&authent=439E1273450650FA2719E8D5BFE9F1>

Dengue exceeds 4000 cases in Ribeirao
-----------------------------------
The city is approaching the [dengue case] mark
registered in 2006, when it had the worst
epidemic of the disease. The number of confirmed
dengue cases in Ribeirao Preto yesterday [16 Mar
2010] reached the mark of 4164, according to the
municipal Secretariat of Health, placing it in
2nd place for the worst epidemic of the disease
there in 11 years. The projection of
Epidemiological Surveillance is that 2010 will
surpass the total number of cases registered the
last 4 years, when 5997 cases were confirmed. The
current number of confirmed cases surpass the
number in the 1st quarter of 2006, when 2156
cases of the disease were reported. As of
yesterday, there have been another 3392 suspected
[cases].

According to the [municipal health] Secretary,
Carla Palhares, the number of [patients] who were
attended for consultations in the Basic Health
Units (UBDSs), as well as those attended in
emergency units of hospitals, have registered an
increase of nearly 30 percent due to dengue. The
UBDSs with most demand are Vila Virginia and
Central. In the 1st, 10 210 persons sought
[medical] attention in the 1st 2 weeks of March
[2010]. In the 2nd, for the same period, 8436
people were attended to.

--
Communicated by
ProMED-PORT
<promed-port@promedmail.org>

[The problem is not limited to the number of
cases. There is dengue [virus] transmission in
localities in which there has not been [dengue]
previously or was of low intensity [such as]:
Distrito Federal, Rio Grande do Sul and
Argentina. The number of deaths increases. -
Mod.LJS]

